01:21.281 --> 01:23.216
♪

01:44.271 --> 01:47.740
Fighter Command, this is
Foxtrot Uniform Charlie Kilo.

01:47.742 --> 01:51.544
I just tiptoed into one hell
of a triple-A shit storm.

01:51.546 --> 01:54.479
Like the freaking
Fourth of July up here.

01:54.481 --> 01:56.751
I got flak coming in
from everywhere.

01:59.252 --> 02:01.388
- Damn it!
- (WHOOSHING)

02:02.489 --> 02:04.523
Mayday, Mayday! I'm hit!

02:04.525 --> 02:07.292
I'm on fire.
Got smoke everywhere.

02:07.294 --> 02:09.227
Smoke coming in.

02:09.229 --> 02:11.764
Got no control.

02:11.766 --> 02:13.699
There's a river
and a swamp below.

02:13.701 --> 02:15.670
I'm gonna ditch her there.

02:19.507 --> 02:21.208
Atta baby.

02:31.819 --> 02:33.953
I'm going in.

02:33.955 --> 02:35.923
(WHOOPING)

02:37.290 --> 02:39.393
(CONTINUES WHOOPING)

02:45.900 --> 02:47.769
(GRUNTS)

02:51.806 --> 02:53.240
(SIGHS)

02:55.843 --> 02:57.710
(BURBLING)

02:57.712 --> 02:59.612
(GRUNTS)

02:59.614 --> 03:00.980
(STEAM HISSING)

03:00.982 --> 03:03.818
(SIGHING)

03:05.787 --> 03:09.322
- Son of a...
- (CLATTERING)

03:15.963 --> 03:20.200
Lousy Army-issued
goddamn flammable boots.

03:24.005 --> 03:25.807
♪

03:43.024 --> 03:44.959
♪

03:53.901 --> 03:56.635
(SNICKERS)

03:56.637 --> 03:58.940
Frilly underthings.

04:12.787 --> 04:14.989
(WHISTLES)

04:17.791 --> 04:19.560
Not bad.

04:21.495 --> 04:23.095
Hmm.

04:23.097 --> 04:24.799
Not bad at all.

04:28.536 --> 04:30.303
<i>Wen haben wir denn hier?</i>

04:31.939 --> 04:33.906
<i>Einen Amerikaner.</i>

04:33.908 --> 04:37.643
That's right, Fritz,
an Ameri-can-doer.

04:37.645 --> 04:39.747
(GUNS COCKING)

04:42.617 --> 04:44.451
<i>Hände nach oben.</i>

04:45.586 --> 04:48.020
Sorry, I don't speak Nazi.

04:48.022 --> 04:49.690
Hands up.

04:54.361 --> 04:56.296
<i>Die Pistole.</i>

05:04.005 --> 05:05.740
<i>Kommen Sie mal her.</i>

05:18.385 --> 05:21.556
<i>Kommen Sie her.</i>

05:31.065 --> 05:32.932
What?

05:32.934 --> 05:34.700
(LAUGHING)

05:34.702 --> 05:36.836
<i>Ein schmutziges
amerikanisches Schwein!</i>

05:36.838 --> 05:38.506
(SOLDIERS LAUGHING)

05:40.407 --> 05:42.641
Go ahead!

05:42.643 --> 05:45.077
Laugh it up, Heinie.

05:45.079 --> 05:47.414
But these heels ain't for sale.

05:50.785 --> 05:55.688
Since you obviously would
rather like to be <i>eine frau,</i>

05:55.690 --> 05:59.124
perhaps we should cut off
your <i>schwanz.</i>

05:59.126 --> 06:01.093
Oh, yeah?

06:01.095 --> 06:03.128
Well, <i>schwanz</i> this.

06:03.130 --> 06:05.164
(CLUNK, HIGH-PITCHED GROANING)

06:05.166 --> 06:06.966
(SOLDIER GRUNTS FIERCELY)

06:06.968 --> 06:08.534
(GROANING)

06:08.536 --> 06:10.669
<i>Tritt dem Homo in die Fresse!</i>

06:10.671 --> 06:13.708
(SOLDIERS LAUGHING,
MUTTERING IN GERMAN)

06:15.610 --> 06:17.745
(GRUNTING)

06:20.480 --> 06:21.714
(GROWLS)

06:21.716 --> 06:23.150
(RAPID GUNFIRE)

06:36.764 --> 06:37.997
(SOLDIER YELLS)

06:37.999 --> 06:39.834
(LAST SHOT ECHOES)

06:46.540 --> 06:48.475
♪

07:03.658 --> 07:05.593
♪

07:19.040 --> 07:20.973
Who are you?

07:20.975 --> 07:23.575
My name is Wendy,

07:23.577 --> 07:26.714
and you are saved.

07:30.885 --> 07:32.153
(CLICK)

07:33.888 --> 07:36.221
MARK (CHUCKLES):
Hey, looking good.

07:36.223 --> 07:37.692
(CLICK)

07:41.996 --> 07:43.965
(LARGE VEHICLE APPROACHING)

07:45.900 --> 07:48.867
Oh, no.
No, no, no, no, no, no.

07:48.869 --> 07:51.105
(SIGHS) Jesus.

07:52.873 --> 07:54.640
(GROANS)

07:54.642 --> 07:56.875
Damn.

07:56.877 --> 07:59.113
You got to be kidding me.

08:01.148 --> 08:03.315
(SIGHS, GROANS)

08:03.317 --> 08:05.019
Well...

08:06.120 --> 08:07.586
Shit.

08:07.588 --> 08:09.256
I guess I got it.

08:10.691 --> 08:12.593
(TAKES DEEP BREATH)

08:14.729 --> 08:18.263
Yeah, I think
I finally got it right.

08:18.265 --> 08:20.801
After all these years...

08:22.870 --> 08:25.039
How long has it been?

08:26.173 --> 08:28.040
Three? Three years.

08:28.042 --> 08:29.643
Jesus.

08:43.657 --> 08:46.759
Three years.

08:46.761 --> 08:49.294
Time flies
when you're having fun.

08:49.296 --> 08:50.865
Right, Hogie?

08:59.140 --> 09:01.609
I'll put the pumps in the bar.

09:21.395 --> 09:23.395
♪

09:23.397 --> 09:25.332
(WATER FLOWING GENTLY)

09:43.250 --> 09:46.620
(GRUNTING)

10:09.877 --> 10:11.812
♪

10:14.982 --> 10:18.219
Sorry, Wendy,
you have to go back.

10:19.753 --> 10:22.289
That was then; this is now.

10:31.732 --> 10:33.667
♪

10:47.181 --> 10:49.183
How you doing, Deja?

10:52.786 --> 10:55.222
- Um...
- (HORN HONKING OUTSIDE)

11:05.766 --> 11:07.299
WOMAN:
Hi.

11:07.301 --> 11:09.301
You got here so fast.

11:09.303 --> 11:11.872
Just one sec.
I have to unlock the door.

11:19.046 --> 11:20.381
(GASPS)

11:30.824 --> 11:33.227
(WHISPERS):
Keep your head down, Deja.

11:38.399 --> 11:41.166
I say she's the new neighbor.

11:41.168 --> 11:43.103
A redhead.

11:44.805 --> 11:48.173
You're just jealous.
You always have been.

11:48.175 --> 11:51.210
Oh! Give me a break.
Are you kidding?

11:51.212 --> 11:54.348
You have been doing
the same thing for centuries.

11:57.818 --> 12:00.052
(CAR APPROACHING)

12:00.054 --> 12:02.790
(LOUD, HEAVY ROCK MUSIC
PLAYING OVER CAR STEREO)

12:03.958 --> 12:05.859
(ENGINE AND MUSIC STOP)

12:09.163 --> 12:11.997
Uh-oh. Here comes trouble.

12:11.999 --> 12:14.567
- Nicol?
- (CLOSES CAR DOOR)

12:14.569 --> 12:17.236
What's all this? Huh?

12:17.238 --> 12:19.972
I need you to stop, and I
need you to leave right now.

12:19.974 --> 12:21.440
- Leave?
- You have to leave.

12:21.442 --> 12:23.576
- Why?
- You have to stop harassing me.

12:23.578 --> 12:25.511
Her name's Nicol.
That's a nice name.

12:25.513 --> 12:27.045
NICOL:
I'm asking you nicely.

12:27.047 --> 12:28.180
- Okay?
- Hey, hang on, Nicol.

12:28.182 --> 12:29.915
Harassing you? Really?

12:29.917 --> 12:31.950
- Yes, really.
- I come home, you're gone.

12:31.952 --> 12:34.019
- No call. You didn't tell me.
- I need you to leave. I'm...

12:34.021 --> 12:36.054
- What do you think, Deja?
- MAN: I'll go.

12:36.056 --> 12:37.356
If that's what you want,
I'll go.

12:37.358 --> 12:38.924
Yes, I want you to go, Kurt.

12:38.926 --> 12:40.892
All right, I'll go. I'll go.

12:40.894 --> 12:43.264
MARK:
His name is Kurt.

12:44.532 --> 12:46.499
And he's a dick.

12:46.501 --> 12:49.001
(KNOCKING AT DOOR)

12:49.003 --> 12:51.136
- Hi, Anna.
- <i>Dobriy den, Mark.</i>

12:51.138 --> 12:53.774
- I bring grocery and mail.
- (TIRES SQUEAL, CAR DEPARTS)

12:58.379 --> 13:01.547
Here. I bring you timer clock.

13:01.549 --> 13:03.081
- (RINGS)
- Use to breathe.

13:03.083 --> 13:05.450
30 seconds,
no more than one minute,

13:05.452 --> 13:08.453
when you get anxiety, huh?

13:08.455 --> 13:10.590
Mark, how you feel? <i>Horosho?</i>

13:10.592 --> 13:13.959
Okay.
Um, pretty good, I guess.

13:13.961 --> 13:17.563
- And how is Captain Hogie?
- Um...

13:17.565 --> 13:20.165
- The SS beat him.
- Again?

13:20.167 --> 13:22.467
But Wendy and the women
saved him.

13:22.469 --> 13:25.337
Ah, Wendy.
She come back to Marwen?

13:25.339 --> 13:27.339
No, no, she's never
coming back.

13:27.341 --> 13:31.009
I just resurrected her for
an old picture I wanted to fix.

13:31.011 --> 13:33.579
- Picture for show?
- (MARK CLEARS THROAT)

13:33.581 --> 13:35.347
Ah, show looks good.

13:35.349 --> 13:37.149
- You go?
- No way.

13:37.151 --> 13:39.951
That's something Roberta
and her cousin cooked up.

13:39.953 --> 13:41.654
I don't...
I don't want any show.

13:41.656 --> 13:43.889
ANNA:
Not to go is dumb.

13:43.891 --> 13:45.891
Bad choice.

13:45.893 --> 13:47.560
I bring you more meds.

13:47.562 --> 13:49.494
Huh? What happened?

13:49.496 --> 13:52.565
- Why you need more so soon?
- I...

13:52.567 --> 13:56.234
- dropped 'em in the sink.
- Ah, again?

13:56.236 --> 14:00.038
You take only one, <i>da,</i>
only one for day.

14:00.040 --> 14:02.675
Too many is no good,
is dangerous.

14:02.677 --> 14:04.376
(SPEAKS RUSSIAN)

14:04.378 --> 14:06.679
I don't know why your doctor
still gives them.

14:06.681 --> 14:08.413
It's not good.

14:08.415 --> 14:11.483
They're very addicting.
You can be addicted.

14:11.485 --> 14:14.119
So, have you been doing
hand exercise?

14:14.121 --> 14:15.521
- <i>Da.</i>
- Mm-hmm.

14:15.523 --> 14:17.590
And what about eating?

14:17.592 --> 14:19.191
- (CHUCKLING): <i>Da.</i>
- Have you been eating?

14:19.193 --> 14:21.594
- (CHUCKLING)
- <i>Net!</i>

14:21.596 --> 14:23.261
Way too skinskie!

14:23.263 --> 14:25.230
You need meat for bones.

14:25.232 --> 14:27.199
Up. Mm-hmm.

14:27.201 --> 14:28.902
Hey, hey.

14:30.337 --> 14:32.471
Ah. Good.

14:32.473 --> 14:34.005
(MARK GRUNTS SOFTLY)

14:34.007 --> 14:35.407
<i>Horosho.</i>

14:35.409 --> 14:37.376
Okay, I go.

14:37.378 --> 14:40.112
Ah! I forget.

14:40.114 --> 14:42.280
- I see Julie.
- Oh.

14:42.282 --> 14:43.683
Uh, she says hello.

14:43.685 --> 14:45.618
She run Rochester Marathon.

14:45.620 --> 14:47.620
Oh, Julie.

14:47.622 --> 14:49.589
How is she?
Is she still in Ithaca?

14:49.591 --> 14:51.089
<i>Da.</i> And her kids grow.

14:51.091 --> 14:53.024
- Six and eight.
- Six and eight. Wow.

14:53.026 --> 14:54.326
Okay, I go now.

14:54.328 --> 14:57.262
Please, don't lose pills.

14:57.264 --> 14:58.631
And don't be stupid.

14:58.633 --> 15:00.465
- You are an artist.
- Mm.

15:00.467 --> 15:02.670
Go to your show. Be proud.

15:05.507 --> 15:07.441
♪

15:25.159 --> 15:26.626
Okay. All right.

15:26.628 --> 15:29.494
No more playing.
You know the drill.

15:29.496 --> 15:31.363
That's right.
You got it, Mark.

15:31.365 --> 15:33.198
Just one foot in front
of the other.

15:33.200 --> 15:35.467
Come on, baby.
You got it. You got this.

15:35.469 --> 15:37.436
We're gonna be tangoing
next month.

15:37.438 --> 15:39.004
- (MARK GROANING)
- You got... I got you.

15:39.006 --> 15:40.439
I got your back.
I got your back.

15:40.441 --> 15:41.774
I'm not gonna let nothing
happen to you.

15:41.776 --> 15:43.643
- It hurts like hell!
- I know, I know.

15:43.645 --> 15:45.343
But you gotta embrace
that pain, Mark.

15:45.345 --> 15:47.747
- (PAINED WHIMPER)
- You gotta love the pain.

15:47.749 --> 15:50.482
(ECHOING):
You gotta love the pain.

15:50.484 --> 15:52.785
<i>Love the pain.</i>

15:52.787 --> 15:54.722
♪

16:17.645 --> 16:19.581
♪

16:38.065 --> 16:40.635
♪

16:47.742 --> 16:50.475
Hogie...

16:50.477 --> 16:52.477
this is Elsa.

16:52.479 --> 16:54.414
♪

17:04.626 --> 17:06.791
She's a milkmaid.

17:06.794 --> 17:08.528
(SNICKERS)

17:08.530 --> 17:11.696
You found her two klicks east
of the river.

17:11.699 --> 17:14.299
A squad of SS wanted to...

17:14.300 --> 17:18.336
have a sausage party,
but you shot 'em.

17:18.338 --> 17:19.371
(CAMERA CLICKS)

17:19.373 --> 17:21.308
(ENGINE RUMBLING)

17:23.578 --> 17:25.178
(GEAR SHIFTS)

17:28.716 --> 17:30.783
Mister?

17:30.785 --> 17:33.886
Uh, what your name is?

17:33.888 --> 17:35.588
Hogancamp.

17:35.590 --> 17:38.223
Captain Mark Hogancamp,
United States Army Air Corps.

17:38.225 --> 17:40.292
But everybody calls me Hogie.

17:40.294 --> 17:42.095
At your service, mademoiselle.

17:49.804 --> 17:52.505
(TIRES SQUEALING)

17:52.507 --> 17:53.908
(ELSA GASPS)

17:57.779 --> 18:00.347
Mademoiselle, <i>après vous.</i>

18:01.716 --> 18:03.516
Well, here it is.

18:03.518 --> 18:05.751
Beautiful downtown Marwen.

18:05.753 --> 18:07.753
Garden spot of Belgium.

18:07.755 --> 18:10.288
And my little piece of heaven.

18:10.290 --> 18:12.257
It's got everything you need.

18:12.259 --> 18:14.459
Fountain, boulangerie,

18:14.461 --> 18:15.895
church, of course,

18:15.897 --> 18:19.331
market, hotel, sidewalk cafe.

18:19.333 --> 18:21.466
And right over there
is my place,

18:21.468 --> 18:23.368
the world-famous
Ruined Stocking.

18:23.370 --> 18:25.370
Friendliest bar
in all of Europe.

18:25.372 --> 18:26.505
There's Julie.

18:26.507 --> 18:27.840
Hey, Jules, how's tricks?

18:27.842 --> 18:29.542
Suzette, bonjour.

18:29.544 --> 18:31.510
What's shaking with <i>le bacon?</i>

18:31.512 --> 18:33.579
<i>Qui sont-ils?</i>

18:33.581 --> 18:35.948
These beautiful dolls...

18:35.950 --> 18:38.551
these are the Women of Marwen.

18:38.553 --> 18:40.285
(JULIE CHUCKLES QUIETLY)

18:40.287 --> 18:43.488
- Who is the new face?
- She's a milkmaid.

18:43.490 --> 18:45.625
I found her two klicks east
of the river.

18:45.627 --> 18:47.425
A squad of dirty Bosch bastards

18:47.427 --> 18:50.261
were about to have a
sausage party, but I shot 'em.

18:50.263 --> 18:52.399
- Oh.
- Does she have a cow?

18:54.201 --> 18:57.639
Got caught in the crossfire.
Cow-lateral damage.

18:59.473 --> 19:01.843
(LAUGHS)

19:02.944 --> 19:05.210
But what's her story?

19:05.212 --> 19:07.647
Yeah. Can she handle a rod?

19:07.649 --> 19:10.415
No, but she can handle a teat,
that's for sure.

19:10.417 --> 19:11.917
- (LIGHT LAUGHTER)
- She's a milkmaid.

19:11.919 --> 19:14.954
All she knows how to do
is squeeze cow teats.

19:14.956 --> 19:17.723
But you dolls are gonna have
to teach her how to squeeze

19:17.725 --> 19:19.592
the wretched life
out of black-hearted Nazi scum.

19:19.594 --> 19:21.527
But she's soft.

19:21.529 --> 19:24.262
Probably been soaking in milk
her whole life.

19:24.264 --> 19:27.267
- JULIE: Mm-hmm.
- Way too skinskie.

19:30.571 --> 19:32.370
Mm. No meat for bones.

19:32.372 --> 19:34.339
All right, all right,
enough with the "skinskie" bit.

19:34.341 --> 19:35.741
All you dolls are skinskie.

19:35.743 --> 19:38.778
And I hate to pull rank here,
but she stays.

19:38.780 --> 19:40.846
Capisce?

19:40.848 --> 19:42.948
- ANNA: Mm-hmm.
- Come on, honey.

19:42.950 --> 19:45.584
I think I have a blouse
that will fit you.

19:45.586 --> 19:49.189
And I've got a pair of capris
that'll look great on you.

19:52.259 --> 19:54.194
♪

20:03.838 --> 20:06.572
ROBERTA:
So, listen, we have rules.

20:06.574 --> 20:09.575
Rule number one:
Never get too close to Hogie.

20:09.577 --> 20:11.944
That's sure to get you killed.

20:11.946 --> 20:14.347
<i>Un moment, s'il vous plaît.</i>

20:15.583 --> 20:17.583
Captain!

20:17.585 --> 20:18.984
Thank you.

20:18.986 --> 20:21.921
- <i>Merci. Merci.</i>
- HOGIE: No.

20:21.923 --> 20:23.288
Don't.

20:23.290 --> 20:24.726
Don't. Don't!

20:27.695 --> 20:30.598
- (GUNSHOT) - Don't!
- (ELSA GASPS, WHIMPERS)

20:31.699 --> 20:32.998
The church!

20:33.000 --> 20:34.902
- In the steeple!
- (GUNS COCKING)

20:36.904 --> 20:37.972
(BELL RINGING REPEATEDLY)

20:45.345 --> 20:47.713
(GROANING)

20:47.715 --> 20:48.850
(SCREAMS)

20:55.623 --> 20:56.956
Hang in there, doll.

20:56.958 --> 20:58.924
We'll have you fixed up
in no time.

20:58.926 --> 21:00.926
She's losing a lot of blood.

21:00.928 --> 21:03.965
Captain... <i>merci.</i>

21:06.000 --> 21:07.702
<i>Merci.</i>

21:12.439 --> 21:14.472
(WOMEN GASPING, CRYING)

21:14.474 --> 21:16.374
Poor kid.

21:16.376 --> 21:18.844
That lousy Kraut slug
was meant for me.

21:18.846 --> 21:21.448
WOMAN:
That's right, my love.

21:23.017 --> 21:25.951
That bullet was meant for you.

21:25.953 --> 21:27.553
HOGIE:
I'm warning you, Deja.

21:27.555 --> 21:30.558
Let's not start
some big commotion here.

21:31.659 --> 21:34.727
What do you mean, my love?

21:34.729 --> 21:37.730
I'm your salvation,
your protector.

21:37.732 --> 21:40.465
I saved you.

21:40.467 --> 21:43.803
Women are hopelessly
attracted to you.

21:43.805 --> 21:46.672
But I will stop
these foolish women!

21:46.674 --> 21:48.974
Back off, witch!

21:48.976 --> 21:52.611
I've heard enough of
your voodoo crap for one day.

21:52.613 --> 21:54.479
Voodoo?

21:54.481 --> 21:56.048
(YELLS)

21:56.050 --> 21:57.885
(WOMEN GASPING)

22:05.458 --> 22:07.458
HOGIE:
Well...

22:07.460 --> 22:10.495
no use crying
over spilled milk.

22:10.497 --> 22:12.432
♪

22:23.410 --> 22:24.877
(GRUNTS)

22:24.879 --> 22:26.745
Jules, what's wrong?

22:26.747 --> 22:28.446
("SPOOKY" BY JOAN OSBORNE
PLAYING OVER SPEAKER)

22:28.448 --> 22:30.149
I don't know. I... (SIGHS)

22:30.151 --> 22:33.484
I just keep thinking about
that poor little milkmaid.

22:33.486 --> 22:35.087
She never knew what hit her.

22:35.089 --> 22:37.656
Like I said,
that slug was meant for me.

22:37.658 --> 22:40.793
No. I'm talking about
after she got shot.

22:40.795 --> 22:43.095
When Deja Thoris
zapped her away.

22:43.097 --> 22:45.064
Poof! Gone.

22:45.066 --> 22:47.566
Just like she did Wendy.

22:47.568 --> 22:49.702
Yeah. Just like Wendy.

22:49.704 --> 22:51.871
ROBERTA:
Look, we all know the story.

22:51.873 --> 22:53.672
This thing with you
and the Belgian Witch

22:53.674 --> 22:56.709
has been going on
for nearly 3,000 years.

22:56.711 --> 22:59.778
The dewy-eyed little milkmaid
got a little too close.

22:59.780 --> 23:01.146
That's all.

23:01.148 --> 23:04.049
<i>Da.</i> Way too close.

23:04.051 --> 23:05.818
But what about us?

23:05.820 --> 23:08.888
When are we going to get
poofed away to who-knows-where?

23:08.890 --> 23:11.523
Ixnay, ixnay.

23:11.525 --> 23:14.894
She could be hearing us.

23:14.896 --> 23:17.763
Dolls, dolls, listen up.

23:17.765 --> 23:19.632
Here's what you got
to remember.

23:19.634 --> 23:23.068
We, us, we're here right now.

23:23.070 --> 23:26.705
We're still alive,
and that's what matters.

23:26.707 --> 23:28.207
So a toast.

23:28.209 --> 23:32.511
To life, to love, to Marwen.

23:32.513 --> 23:34.582
And the beautiful women
thereof.

23:36.951 --> 23:38.150
(CLICK)

23:38.152 --> 23:40.653
♪ And if a fella looks at you

23:40.655 --> 23:45.760
♪ Well, it's for sure your
little eyes will be a-winking ♪

23:49.530 --> 23:51.196
♪ I get confused

23:51.198 --> 23:53.699
♪ 'Cause I don't know
where I stand ♪

23:53.701 --> 23:55.034
♪ And then you smile...

23:55.036 --> 23:56.804
There you are.

23:58.873 --> 24:02.541
You sneaky little witch.

24:02.543 --> 24:05.811
All right, girls,
time to hit the hay.

24:05.813 --> 24:07.680
(MUSIC STOPS)

24:07.682 --> 24:09.150
Rack time.

24:14.021 --> 24:15.957
(PHONE RINGING)

24:18.159 --> 24:20.594
(TRAIN WHISTLE BLOWING
IN DISTANCE)

24:22.930 --> 24:24.763
(ANSWERING MACHINE
BEEPS, CLICKS)

24:24.765 --> 24:27.199
WOMAN (RECORDED): Hello. You
have reached Mark Hogancamp.

24:27.201 --> 24:29.001
He can't get to the phone
right now,

24:29.003 --> 24:30.903
but if you leave your name
and number,

24:30.905 --> 24:32.972
he'll get right back to you.

24:32.974 --> 24:35.941
(BEEP, CLICKING)

24:35.943 --> 24:39.545
MAN:
Mark, it's Demaryius Johnson.

24:39.547 --> 24:42.281
Listen, I'm sorry
to be calling so late.

24:42.283 --> 24:46.919
And I assume you're monitoring,
so I'll try to be brief.

24:46.921 --> 24:48.954
Listen, um, I don't know
if you remember,

24:48.956 --> 24:51.890
but the sentencing
is on the 13th, Friday.

24:51.892 --> 24:53.692
And, as we discussed
many times,

24:53.694 --> 24:56.028
it's vitally important
that you be there,

24:56.030 --> 24:58.330
that you be in court that day.

24:58.332 --> 25:00.799
We want the judge to hand down
the maximum sentence,

25:00.801 --> 25:02.935
so it's-it's important
that you're there.

25:02.937 --> 25:04.303
(SHUDDERING)

25:04.305 --> 25:06.105
To look your assailant
straight in the eye

25:06.107 --> 25:09.608
and for the judge to see you
face your attackers.

25:09.610 --> 25:12.044
(GROWING LOUDER): They need to
pay for what they did to you.

25:12.046 --> 25:14.113
I want the judge
to throw the book at them.

25:14.115 --> 25:16.115
(DISTORTED, STUTTERING):
I want the judge

25:16.117 --> 25:18.617
to throw the book at them.

25:18.619 --> 25:21.589
(HEAVY GUNFIRE, GASPING)

25:24.158 --> 25:26.058
- Hit the dirt!
- HOGIE: Hit the dirt!

25:26.060 --> 25:28.162
We got Heinies swarming
everywhere!

25:50.251 --> 25:51.185
(GASPS)

25:54.321 --> 25:55.954
(GUN CLICKING)

25:55.956 --> 25:57.689
I'm out!

25:57.691 --> 25:59.625
I need more ammo!

25:59.627 --> 26:00.961
More ammo!

26:02.763 --> 26:05.931
- More ammo! We need more ammo!
- (KNOCKING AT DOOR)

26:05.933 --> 26:08.400
Goddamn it, get me more ammo!

26:08.402 --> 26:10.402
- NICOL: Hello?
- (GUNFIRE STOPS)

26:10.404 --> 26:12.671
Is everything okay?

26:12.673 --> 26:15.074
(SHUDDERING)

26:15.076 --> 26:17.078
I heard screaming.

26:18.979 --> 26:21.246
Are you all right?

26:21.248 --> 26:22.817
(WHIMPERS)

26:25.052 --> 26:28.153
Yes. Okay.

26:28.155 --> 26:32.159
I thought I heard you yelling
for more gumbo.

26:34.328 --> 26:36.061
No.

26:36.063 --> 26:37.631
Not gumbo.

26:38.699 --> 26:40.232
No gumbo.

26:40.234 --> 26:43.170
Okay. Sorry for disturbing you.

26:46.173 --> 26:48.140
(WHIMPERS)

26:48.142 --> 26:50.177
(PANTING)

26:51.712 --> 26:53.647
♪

27:00.955 --> 27:03.021
DEJA:
<i>I love you.</i>

27:03.023 --> 27:05.858
Come away with me.

27:05.860 --> 27:09.728
(ECHOING):
I will love you forever.

27:09.730 --> 27:15.367
I alone am the one
who has the power to help you.

27:15.369 --> 27:20.038
Only I can stop your pain.

27:20.040 --> 27:21.740
(GASPS)

27:21.742 --> 27:24.879
(TRAIN WHISTLE BLOWING
IN DISTANCE)

27:29.950 --> 27:32.751
(SIGHS)

27:32.753 --> 27:35.723
(FAUCET SQUEAKING,
DOG BARKING IN DISTANCE)

27:57.945 --> 27:59.845
(BELL RINGING)

27:59.847 --> 28:01.782
♪

28:04.818 --> 28:07.386
Rise and shine!
Rise and shine!

28:07.388 --> 28:09.855
Out of your box,
and grab your socks.

28:09.857 --> 28:11.423
It is Thursday.

28:11.425 --> 28:13.792
We have work to do.

28:13.794 --> 28:15.460
- (SUZETTE YAWNING)
- I suggest that you rise

28:15.462 --> 28:17.029
from the prone position.

28:17.031 --> 28:18.430
Can you hear me?

28:18.432 --> 28:20.132
- <i>Da!</i>
- Yes, sir!

28:20.134 --> 28:21.534
Keep your eyes peeled.

28:21.536 --> 28:23.769
Lousy bastards
could be anywhere.

28:23.771 --> 28:25.804
Carlala, keep your eyes
on the road.

28:25.806 --> 28:27.306
Jules, shoot anything
that moves.

28:27.308 --> 28:28.943
Wilco, Cap'n.

28:40.087 --> 28:42.122
("CRAZY" BY PATSY CLINE
PLAYING)

28:54.034 --> 28:56.268
♪ Crazy

28:56.270 --> 28:59.871
- ♪ I'm crazy for feeling...
- (BELL JINGLING)

28:59.873 --> 29:02.341
- Hi, Larry.
- Hey, Mark.

29:02.343 --> 29:04.109
Carlala's looking for you.

29:04.111 --> 29:06.945
- And, uh, tell her I need more limes.
- Roger.

29:06.947 --> 29:09.248
And don't forget, uh,
Thursday's meatball day.

29:09.250 --> 29:11.250
Roger. Meatball day.

29:11.252 --> 29:12.818
CARLALA:
Hey, Mark.

29:12.820 --> 29:14.587
- So that's the guy?
- Yeah.

29:14.589 --> 29:16.154
He was right out there,

29:16.156 --> 29:18.123
right in the middle
of the road.

29:18.125 --> 29:20.158
Five of 'em jumped him.

29:20.160 --> 29:21.994
It's a miracle he survived.

29:21.996 --> 29:26.298
Wendy, the woman who used to
tend bar here, she found him.

29:26.300 --> 29:30.168
Thought he was a freaking
garbage bag until he moved.

29:30.170 --> 29:33.205
MARK:
Let me tell you, Carlala,

29:33.207 --> 29:35.207
Deja vanquished her.

29:35.209 --> 29:37.610
(CHUCKLES)
So she just zapped her away?

29:37.612 --> 29:39.444
- Yep, just like that.
- (SNAPS FINGERS)

29:39.446 --> 29:42.047
- Just like Wendy.
- Wow.

29:42.049 --> 29:45.917
That Deja Thoris is a real
piece of work, isn't she?

29:45.919 --> 29:48.420
But I don't understand;
why is she being so weird?

29:48.422 --> 29:51.223
She loves Hogie.
She wants him for herself.

29:51.225 --> 29:53.859
Mark, can I ask you a question?

29:53.861 --> 29:56.094
How come I have to be alone
in Marwen?

29:56.096 --> 29:57.262
Hmm?

29:57.264 --> 29:59.364
Don't I ever get a lover?

29:59.366 --> 30:01.300
You never know.

30:01.302 --> 30:04.469
Patton's Third Army may be
rolling through anytime now.

30:04.471 --> 30:06.471
Well, if that happens,
make sure to keep

30:06.473 --> 30:09.074
that Belgian Witch
far away from my man.

30:09.076 --> 30:12.377
Nah. Deja only cares
about Hogie.

30:12.379 --> 30:15.447
She's obsessed with him.

30:15.449 --> 30:21.086
♪ How long must I dream?

30:21.088 --> 30:24.089
Do you ever hear
from Wendy anymore?

30:24.091 --> 30:26.626
LARRY:
<i>Wendy, do you take Hogie</i>

30:26.628 --> 30:28.528
<i>to be your lawfully
wedded husband,</i>

30:28.530 --> 30:31.129
<i>until death do you part?</i>

30:31.131 --> 30:33.031
- I do.
- ♪ Gonna get married...

30:33.033 --> 30:37.503
Then, by the power vested in me
by the Kingdom of Belgium

30:37.505 --> 30:41.440
and by the supreme commander of
the Allied Expeditionary Force,

30:41.442 --> 30:44.409
I now declare you man and wife.

30:44.411 --> 30:46.912
You may kiss the bride.

30:46.914 --> 30:49.515
- (WHOOSHING)
- CARLALA: She moved on.

30:49.517 --> 30:51.083
What?

30:51.085 --> 30:53.051
What did you say?

30:53.053 --> 30:55.053
I said, "She moved on."

30:55.055 --> 30:57.523
I heard she moved
to California.

30:57.525 --> 30:59.925
♪ Sweet dream baby...

30:59.927 --> 31:02.027
Oh, yeah, right.
California.

31:02.029 --> 31:05.130
♪ Sweet dream baby

31:05.132 --> 31:07.366
♪ Dream baby, uh-huh

31:07.368 --> 31:10.505
- ♪ How long must I dream?
- (BELL JINGLING)

31:18.613 --> 31:20.212
Mark.

31:20.214 --> 31:22.013
- Hello.
- Hello, Roberta.

31:22.015 --> 31:23.583
I'm making some coffee.
You want some?

31:23.585 --> 31:25.350
No, thank you.

31:25.352 --> 31:28.220
Jeep looks good.
Mud splatter's really cool.

31:28.222 --> 31:31.289
Mm. It's gonna take a long time
and a lot of miles

31:31.291 --> 31:35.193
to get the right amount of wear
on those tires.

31:35.195 --> 31:37.563
The coffee's good stuff...
dark roast Colombian.

31:37.565 --> 31:40.031
Oh, no,
I've had enough already today.

31:40.033 --> 31:42.033
All you ever drink is coffee
all day long.

31:42.035 --> 31:44.269
Yeah, I need to cut down
on my caffeine, I think.

31:44.271 --> 31:46.606
- It's decaf.
- Well, I'm kind of in a hurry, so...

31:46.608 --> 31:49.374
- It's instant.
- Um, oh-oh... yeah, okay.

31:49.376 --> 31:50.676
Yeah, instant decaf.

31:50.678 --> 31:52.277
Great.
It'll be ready in a jiffy.

31:52.279 --> 31:53.615
Okay.

32:01.388 --> 32:03.422
- Hey, Mark.
- Hmm?

32:03.424 --> 32:06.592
My mom's baking a ham
on Sunday.

32:06.594 --> 32:09.494
Do you want to come over
for dinner?

32:09.496 --> 32:11.697
Ham? Your house?

32:11.699 --> 32:13.633
Well, it's my mom's house.

32:13.635 --> 32:15.501
But, yeah, my house.

32:15.503 --> 32:17.670
Um... yeah, I don't know.

32:17.672 --> 32:19.772
I'm-I'm not really crazy
about ham.

32:19.774 --> 32:22.542
That's okay. I'm sure she'd
be happy to roast a chicken.

32:22.544 --> 32:25.343
Ugh. I'm not crazy
about chicken, either.

32:25.345 --> 32:28.447
- How about pot roast?
- Uh, that gives me gas.

32:28.449 --> 32:31.082
- Ribs?
- That's kind of messy. Um...

32:31.084 --> 32:32.119
Sushi?

32:35.155 --> 32:37.122
Your mom can make sushi?

32:37.124 --> 32:39.391
No. But we can find
a place to get it.

32:39.393 --> 32:41.293
Actually, I've...

32:41.295 --> 32:43.529
I've never tried sushi.

32:43.531 --> 32:46.099
But I'd be happy
to go with you.

32:48.368 --> 32:50.202
I've never tried it, either.

32:50.204 --> 32:51.470
- Oh.
- Um...

32:51.472 --> 32:54.306
Wow. Look at that.

32:54.308 --> 32:56.475
It's another thing
we have in common.

32:56.477 --> 32:59.112
Neither of us
has ever had sushi.

33:01.348 --> 33:04.483
I'm looking for a
Glamonista doll with red hair.

33:04.485 --> 33:06.351
A redhead?

33:06.353 --> 33:08.588
I thought you liked blondes.

33:08.590 --> 33:10.523
Yeah, but I need a redhead.

33:10.525 --> 33:12.725
- Oh, yeah.
- How about this one?

33:12.727 --> 33:14.125
Yeah.

33:14.127 --> 33:16.428
Oh, good eyes.

33:16.430 --> 33:18.598
Nice paint job.

33:18.600 --> 33:20.465
What are you gonna name her?

33:20.467 --> 33:23.736
- Scarlet?
- No, Nicol.

33:23.738 --> 33:25.673
- Nicol, huh?
- Mm-hmm.

33:27.441 --> 33:29.474
Come on, Nicol,
let's ring you up.

33:29.476 --> 33:31.646
- Put her on your tab?
- Yeah.

33:34.314 --> 33:38.450
Oh, hey, are you excited
about your show?

33:38.452 --> 33:40.820
My cousin is thrilled.

33:40.822 --> 33:43.556
And so is everybody
at the gallery.

33:43.558 --> 33:45.423
Oh.

33:45.425 --> 33:47.361
Check this out.

33:49.396 --> 33:52.497
This SS general just came in.

33:52.499 --> 33:54.366
High-end figures are so cool.

33:54.368 --> 33:56.536
They're so beautifully
detailed.

33:56.538 --> 34:00.138
Do you want me
to wrap it up, too?

34:00.140 --> 34:01.541
No.

34:01.543 --> 34:03.241
♪

34:03.243 --> 34:04.644
I can't... I...

34:04.646 --> 34:06.679
I can't afford this.

34:06.681 --> 34:11.483
It says here he's
a major general Waffen-SS.

34:11.485 --> 34:13.385
Fought in Belgium in 1944.

34:13.387 --> 34:15.821
Isn't that a coincidence?

34:15.822 --> 34:18.456
Name's Kurt. Kurt Meyer.

34:18.458 --> 34:20.425
REPORTER (OVER TV): ...for
the five assailants convicted

34:20.427 --> 34:21.793
of the beating of local artist

34:21.795 --> 34:23.295
and photographer
Mark Hogancamp.

34:23.297 --> 34:25.697
- (GASPS)
- Let's go live to Jennifer Cook,

34:25.699 --> 34:27.399
- who's at the Ulster County Courthouse...
- I'm sorry, Mark!

34:27.400 --> 34:28.900
- I'll get the remote!
- ...with the latest update.

34:28.902 --> 34:30.902
- Jennifer?
- (TEAKETTLE WHISTLING)

34:30.905 --> 34:32.505
Yes, Bill,
I've just been informed

34:32.507 --> 34:34.306
Judge Harter
has revoked the request

34:34.308 --> 34:35.908
for a further
psychiatric evaluation

34:35.909 --> 34:37.543
of one of the defendants.

34:37.545 --> 34:40.545
The sentencing
will proceed as scheduled

34:40.547 --> 34:42.213
for the five
convicted assailants

34:42.215 --> 34:44.248
responsible
for the brutal attack

34:44.251 --> 34:47.152
of the local artist
Mark Hogancamp.

34:47.154 --> 34:48.822
(TEAKETTLE CONTINUES WHISTLING)

34:53.761 --> 34:56.194
For crying out loud, Carlala,

34:56.196 --> 34:58.396
what do you think this is,
the Indy 500?!

34:58.398 --> 35:00.334
I'm only doing 80.

35:08.643 --> 35:11.409
(WHISTLING CONTINUES)

35:11.411 --> 35:13.313
I'm sorry, Mark.

35:23.558 --> 35:25.492
♪

35:42.409 --> 35:45.911
DEJA (ECHOING):
Take this medicine, <i>mein</i> love.

35:45.913 --> 35:49.548
It will make you feel better.

35:49.550 --> 35:52.785
I know how much you suffer.

35:52.787 --> 35:55.721
How much it hurts.

35:55.723 --> 35:58.826
How much pain you've endured.

36:01.596 --> 36:04.864
I will always be there for you.

36:04.866 --> 36:08.801
I'm the only one you can trust.

36:08.803 --> 36:12.505
The only one
who understands you.

36:12.507 --> 36:16.307
The only one who feels
your pain.

36:16.309 --> 36:20.345
The only one who loves you.

36:20.347 --> 36:23.481
Take this medicine, <i>mein</i> love.

36:23.483 --> 36:28.654
<i>Take this medicine.
Take this medicine.</i>

36:28.656 --> 36:30.690
- Get away from me now!
- Ooh! - <i>Du dumme Schlampe!</i>

36:30.692 --> 36:33.324
- (LAUGHTER)
- <i>Du dumme Schlampe!</i>

36:33.326 --> 36:34.696
- <i>Das reicht.</i>
- (LAUGHTER STOPS)

36:36.496 --> 36:38.296
<i>Bitte, mein Fräulein.</i>

36:38.298 --> 36:41.466
Just tell us where we can find
your Cap'n Hogie,

36:41.468 --> 36:43.401
and we will be on our way.

36:43.403 --> 36:44.837
I promise.

36:44.839 --> 36:47.006
Get your mitts off me,
you filthy scum.

36:47.008 --> 36:48.473
- SOLDIERS: Oh!
- (GUN COCKS)

36:48.475 --> 36:50.543
HOGIE:
You heard her, scum.

36:50.545 --> 36:52.343
Get your filthy mitts
off of her.

36:52.345 --> 36:53.713
<i>Schnell!</i>

36:53.715 --> 36:55.346
Come on.

36:55.348 --> 36:56.582
Get 'em up.

36:56.584 --> 36:58.483
Reach for the sky.

36:58.485 --> 37:00.485
Let me see
a two-handed <i>"Sieg heil,"</i>

37:00.487 --> 37:01.754
you box-headed Rhine monkeys.

37:01.756 --> 37:03.055
(LAUGHING)

37:03.057 --> 37:05.258
Same goes for you, four-eyes.

37:06.761 --> 37:08.361
(GRUNTING AND GROANING)

37:15.837 --> 37:17.970
- (CLICK)
- ROBERTA: Hey.

37:17.972 --> 37:19.841
Where's my top?

37:22.777 --> 37:25.745
- What happened to my top?
- The Nazis ripped it off.

37:25.747 --> 37:27.012
Again?

37:27.014 --> 37:28.981
I know.

37:28.983 --> 37:31.284
It never ends with these guys.

37:33.521 --> 37:36.354
Hey, I brought your doll.

37:36.356 --> 37:39.525
You left in kind of
a hurry yesterday.

37:39.527 --> 37:41.560
What was her name again?

37:41.562 --> 37:42.862
- Nicol.
- Oh.

37:42.864 --> 37:44.395
Thanks.

37:44.397 --> 37:46.999
And I found these
in the thrift shop.

37:47.001 --> 37:48.868
- Oh, wedges!
- Yeah.

37:48.870 --> 37:50.503
- Oh!
- Definitely vintage.

37:50.505 --> 37:52.838
1960s, size 11.

37:52.840 --> 37:55.040
- Mm.
- The lady in the shop

37:55.042 --> 37:57.076
said they were espadrilles.

37:57.078 --> 37:59.845
Cool. Espadrille wedges.

37:59.847 --> 38:02.081
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

38:02.083 --> 38:05.117
I felt bad about
the TV yesterday.

38:05.119 --> 38:07.653
You seemed pretty freaked out.

38:07.655 --> 38:09.454
You taking your meds?

38:09.456 --> 38:11.391
- Mm-hmm.
- Good.

38:12.760 --> 38:15.060
So, are you gonna go
to the sentencing?

38:15.062 --> 38:16.962
I doubt it.

38:16.964 --> 38:19.430
I'll go with you, if you want.

38:19.432 --> 38:21.000
Uh-uh.

38:21.002 --> 38:22.868
It's important.

38:22.870 --> 38:25.403
You need to go.

38:25.405 --> 38:28.373
So those jerks get
what they deserve.

38:28.375 --> 38:29.975
You can't let them
get off lightly.

38:29.977 --> 38:32.580
I mean, they ruined your life,
for cripes sake.

38:33.681 --> 38:35.482
I can't.

38:38.920 --> 38:42.855
I can't be in the same room.

38:42.857 --> 38:47.427
I understand, but running away
is not helping you any.

38:52.166 --> 38:54.166
Oh, hey.

38:54.168 --> 38:56.602
Are you sure you don't want
the SS doll?

38:56.604 --> 38:58.904
It's better-made than any
of the high-end action figures

38:58.906 --> 39:01.472
or even the Glamonistas.

39:01.474 --> 39:04.810
Did someone say "Glamonistas"?

39:04.812 --> 39:07.847
I... Uh, the gate was open.
I hope it's okay.

39:07.849 --> 39:10.516
I... I love Glamonistas.

39:10.518 --> 39:12.518
I hope I'm not interrupting.

39:12.520 --> 39:14.820
I, um... I just moved in
across the street.

39:14.822 --> 39:16.989
I just wanted to say hello.

39:16.991 --> 39:19.424
I'm Nicol.

39:19.426 --> 39:20.826
- Hi.
- Hey.

39:20.828 --> 39:22.964
I'm Roberta. This is Mark.

