All right.

01:07:13.100 --> 01:07:14.867
Oh, God.

01:07:14.869 --> 01:07:18.205
(WHIMPERING)

01:07:25.647 --> 01:07:27.582
(INSECTS CHIRPING)

01:07:31.418 --> 01:07:33.719
It's such a beautiful moon.

01:07:33.721 --> 01:07:35.355
♪

01:07:37.424 --> 01:07:39.424
It sure is.

01:07:39.426 --> 01:07:41.461
Just like you.

01:07:44.799 --> 01:07:47.667
- Hey, Hogie.
- Mm-hmm?

01:07:47.669 --> 01:07:50.636
I've never been happier.

01:07:50.638 --> 01:07:52.237
Don't.

01:07:52.239 --> 01:07:54.239
It's like
I've been telling you.

01:07:54.241 --> 01:07:56.909
- I'm cursed.
- No.

01:07:56.911 --> 01:07:58.911
Whenever someone I care about
gets too close...

01:07:58.913 --> 01:08:00.445
(KNOCKING AT DOOR, NICOL GASPS)

01:08:00.447 --> 01:08:02.882
- (THUNDER CRASHES)
- HOGIE: Shh.

01:08:02.884 --> 01:08:05.216
We got company.

01:08:05.218 --> 01:08:07.319
(KNOCKING CONTINUES)

01:08:07.321 --> 01:08:09.321
NICOL:
Mark?

01:08:09.323 --> 01:08:11.124
It's Nicol.

01:08:16.898 --> 01:08:18.863
- Hey.
- Hey.

01:08:18.866 --> 01:08:20.832
Tough day yesterday, huh?

01:08:20.835 --> 01:08:23.435
I saw you on TV.

01:08:23.437 --> 01:08:26.872
Um, anyway, I hope
I'm not disturbing you.

01:08:26.874 --> 01:08:28.640
MARK:
Mm.

01:08:28.643 --> 01:08:32.377
I just wanted to apologize
for Kurt's behavior.

01:08:32.379 --> 01:08:33.845
Is that your husband?

01:08:33.848 --> 01:08:36.481
- No. No.
- Is he your boyfriend?

01:08:36.483 --> 01:08:38.183
For, like, ten seconds.

01:08:38.185 --> 01:08:40.720
- He scared the crap out of me.
- Yeah, I know.

01:08:40.721 --> 01:08:42.688
He definitely has his issues.

01:08:42.689 --> 01:08:44.590
(CHUCKLES):
That's for sure.

01:08:44.591 --> 01:08:46.524
I think it's a cop thing.

01:08:46.527 --> 01:08:48.193
He's a cop?

01:08:48.194 --> 01:08:49.729
- Yeah. Well, was a cop.
- (SPUTTERING EXHALE)

01:08:49.731 --> 01:08:51.964
Uh, is it okay
if I come in for a second?

01:08:51.966 --> 01:08:53.499
Oh, yeah, come in.

01:08:53.501 --> 01:08:54.800
Um...

01:08:54.801 --> 01:08:57.335
Yeah, Bomb Squad commander.

01:08:57.337 --> 01:08:59.839
Endicott PD.

01:08:59.841 --> 01:09:03.643
Um, until he got
his second DUI.

01:09:03.645 --> 01:09:05.678
- I...
- Uh, can I take your coat?

01:09:05.680 --> 01:09:08.412
Oh, sure. Thanks.

01:09:08.415 --> 01:09:12.885
Um, anyway, I was
cleaning out my closet.

01:09:12.886 --> 01:09:14.486
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

01:09:14.488 --> 01:09:18.624
And I thought
you might like these.

01:09:18.626 --> 01:09:20.626
Oh.

01:09:20.627 --> 01:09:23.461
(GASPS, CHUCKLES)

01:09:23.462 --> 01:09:25.898
I put a lot of miles
on some of 'em,

01:09:25.899 --> 01:09:27.667
but some of 'em
I only wore once.

01:09:27.669 --> 01:09:30.335
- And those are my old heart spikes.
- (GASPING)

01:09:30.337 --> 01:09:31.970
Are these Christian Louboutin?

01:09:31.973 --> 01:09:33.404
(CHUCKLES):
No.

01:09:33.407 --> 01:09:34.974
They're knock-offs.

01:09:34.975 --> 01:09:37.609
